!!! 1.1
%html
    %head
        %title= @item[:title]

        - # Tiny link for Twitter & co.
        - if @item[:tiny]
            %link(rev="canonical" type="text/html" href="http://mutelight.org#{@item[:tiny]}")
        = render('_static_head')

    %body
        - content = yield
        #radial
            #wrapper
                #header
                    %h1.hide
                        %a(href="http://mutelight.org" title="Mutelight") Mutelight
                - if @item[:kind] == 'article'
                    = render('_article', :item => @item, :content => content)
                    = render('_other_articles', :reference_item => @item)
                - else
                    = content
                #about
                    %h2.hide About
                    %p.important
                        I'm 
                        %strong Brandur Leach, 
                        an engineer and developer operating out of Calgary, Canada doing work primarily in C#/.NET. This is Mutelight &mdash; my weblog. You should follow me on 
                        %a(href="http://twitter.com/fyrerise" title="Brandur on Twitter") Twitter.
                    %p
                        My current learning focus is function languages like Clojure, Erland, Haskell, and F#. At the moment I'm learning Haskell by hacking away on a 
                        %a(href="http://github.com/fyrerise/obsidian" title="Obsidian on GitHub") personal web framework
                        that uses CouchDB as its datastore.
                    %p
                        I like learning guitar, 
                        %a(href="http://flickr.com/photos/brandurleach" title="Brandur on Flickr") photography
                        , 
                        %a(href="http://github.com/fyrerise" title="Brandur on GitHub") coding
                        , 
                        %a(href="http://www.last.fm/user/fyrerise" title="Brandur on last.fm") listening to power and symphonic metal
                        , and tennis. I prefer working on systems with a terminal, but I spend most of my time under Windows at work. Everything that I write is done in Vim.
                    %div#articles
                        %a(href="/archive.html" title="Article archive") Archive &rarr;
                    %p 
                        E-mail me anytime at 
                        %strong.mail brandur@mutelight.org.
                %br
                %br
